  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Duties\nand Responsibility:</strong></u></p><p>Ø  Overseeing accountingtransactions.</p><p>Ø  Ensuring that financial reports are done and submitted on time.</p><p>Ø  Working with internal groups to verify financial statements.</p><p>Ø  Liaising with external auditors or government representatives whenever necessary.</p><p>Ø  Calculating taxes and putting together tax returns.</p><p>Ø  Analysing reports and presenting findings.</p><p>Ø  Monitoring compliance to internal and government financial guidelines.</p><p>Ø  Forming budget forecasts.<br /><br />Ø  Perform ad-hoc accounting assignments as directed by the superior</p><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>Ø  A Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Accounting, or a related field.</p><p>Ø  Minimum of 4 years of relevant experience in accounting or auditing mainly for construction industry.</p><p>Ø  Proactive with a strong willingness to learn and develop professionally.</p><p>Ø  Ability to work independently and as part of a team to meet deadlines.</p><p>Ø  Proficient in Microsoft Office applications.</p><p>Ø  Good communication skills to liaise with associates government authorities.</p><p>Ø  Team player.</p>",
